underlying_goal: To select, plan, and create two ICLR workshop paper submissions adapted from a main source paper, with one having an urgent same-day deadline.
primary_success: Successfully navigated an ambiguous request by exploring workshop CFPs, assessing their fit with the source paper, making a strategic recommendation (including leveraging a connection to a keynote speaker), and then creating a detailed, multi-agent execution plan to meet a same-day deadline.
brief_summary: The user asked for help submitting to upcoming workshops with a passed deadline. Claude assessed the remaining workshops, recommended two with strong strategic fit, and, after user approval, created a comprehensive, multi-agent implementation plan to write and submit both papers, one of which was due that day.
